2000 Nevada Congressional Districts
Redistricting requirements
In Nevada,according to NCSL Redistricting Law 2000, districts must:

be contiguous
have equal populations
Algorithmic Constraints
We enforce a maximum population deviation of 0.5%.

Data Sources
Data for Nevada comes from the ALARM Project's update to The Record of American Democracy.

Pre-processing Notes
No manual pre-processing decisions were necessary.

Simulation Notes
We sample 5,000 districting plans for Nevada. No special techniques were needed to produce the sample.
